.TH COMMAND * 2014-04-08 "SequoiaDB" "Sequoiadb sdb's Manual"
.ad l.ll 72.ce 1000
\fBcursor.explain()\fR
.ce 0
.sp 2

.SH "NAME"

.sp 2
explain - Return the access plan of the current cursor.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.sp 2

.sp 2

.sp 2
cousor.explain()
.SH "CATEGORY"

.sp 2

.sp 2
Cursor
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

.sp 2
Return the access plan of the current cursor.
.sp 2
\fBFullName (string)\fR
.br
       Collection Name.
.sp 2
\fBScanType (string)\fR
.br
       Scanning Type: TableScan: "TBSCAN"; IndexScan:"IXSCAN"
.sp 2
\fBIdxName (string)\fR
.br
       Index name.
.sp 2
\fBUseExtSort (bool)\fR
.br
       Whether use external sort or not.
.sp 2
\fBNode (string)\fR
.br
       Node Name.
.sp 2
\fBReturnNum (int64)\fR
.br
       Number of returned records.
.sp 2
\fBElapsedTime (float64)\fR
.br
       Elapsed Time(seconds).
.sp 2
\fBIdxRead (int64)\fR
.br
       Number of Index read.
.sp 2
\fBDataRead (int64)\fR
.br
       Number of data read.
.sp 2
\fBUsrCpu (float64)\fR
.br
       Time used by cpu in user mode(seconds).
.sp 2
\fBSysCpu (float64)\fR
.br
       Time used by cpu in kernel mode(seconds).
.sp 2
\fBSubCollections (Json Array)\fR
.br
       The access plan of each sub-collections of the
       vertical-partitioning collection.
.sp 2
\fBNote: \fR
.sp 2
   *  If the collection is splitted into different replica
   groups, each replica group will return its own access plan
   correspondingly.
.SH "Examples"

.sp 2
Suppose foo.bar is a horizontal-partitioning collection splitted
in three replica groups.
.sp 2
db.foo.bar.find().sort({b:1}).explain()
.sp 2
Return:
.sp 2
{
.br
  "FullName": "foo.bar",
.br
  "ScanType": "TBSCAN",
.br
  "IdxName": "",
.br
  "UseExtSort": true,
.br
  "Node": "vmsvr2-cent-x64:40020",
.br
  "ReturnNum": 0,
.br
  "ElapsedTime": 0.000477,
.br
  "IdxRead": 0,
.br
  "DataRead": 38,
.br
  "UsrCpu": 0,
.br
  "SysCpu": 0
.br
}
.br
{
.br
  "FullName": "foo.bar",
.br
